    "Normally, the observation represents the state itself.",
    "• Partial observability model: ((s t-l+1,..., s t), a t) → (s t+1, r t).",
    "The lack of information in the current observation can be mitigated by considering the history of previous observations.",
    "• Multi-step prediction model: (s t, (a t,..., a t+l-1)) → (s t+l, ∑ t+l-1 t r t).",
    "Multi-step predic- tions by repeatedly applying one-step prediction models can accumulate errors because the one-step model is not learned to optimize long-term predictions."
